description:
`bigip_ltm_profile_tcp` Configures a custom profile_tcp for use by health checks.

Resources should be named with their "full path". The full path is the combination of the partition + name (example: /Common/my-pool ) or  partition + directory + name of the resource  (example: /Common/test/my-pool )

tfcfnid.description: Internal identifier for tracking resource changes. Do not use.

CloseWaitTimeout.description: Specifies the number of seconds that a connection remains in a LAST-ACK state before quitting. A value of 0 represents a term of forever (or until the maxrtx of the FIN state). The default value is 5 seconds.

DefaultsFrom.description: Specifies the profile that you want to use as the parent profile. Your new profile inherits all settings and values from the parent profile specified.

DeferredAccept.description: Specifies, when enabled, that the system defers allocation of the connection chain context until the client response is received. This option is useful for dealing with 3-way handshake DOS attacks. The default value is disabled.

FastOpen.description: When enabled, permits TCP Fast Open, allowing properly equipped TCP clients to send data with the SYN packet.

Finwait2timeout.description: Specifies the number of seconds that a connection is in the FIN-WAIT-2 state before quitting. The default value is 300 seconds. A value of 0 (zero) represents a term of forever (or until the maxrtx of the FIN state).

FinwaitTimeout.description: Specifies the number of seconds that a connection is in the FIN-WAIT-1 or closing state before quitting. The default value is 5 seconds. A value of 0 (zero) represents a term of forever (or until the maxrtx of the FIN state). You can also specify immediate or indefinite.

IdleTimeout.description: Specifies the number of seconds that a connection is idle before the connection is eligible for deletion. The default value is 300 seconds.

KeepaliveInterval.description: Specifies the keep alive probe interval, in seconds. The default value is 1800 seconds.

Partition.description: Displays the administrative partition within which this profile resides.
